    <section class="hero">
      <div class="hero-kicker">Future scenario timeline</div>
      <h1>World War III & The New Order (2026–2045)</h1>
      <p class="hero-tagline">
        A speculative, integrated chronology of a third world war starting in Europe,
        China’s expansion across Eastern Asia, a Caribbean build-up, the attack on Australia,
        and the birth of a new global security system.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span>Scope: 2026–2045</span>
        <span>Regions: Europe · Indo-Pacific · Caribbean · North America</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="intro">
      <h2>A wormhole into one possible mid-21st-century future</h2>
      <p>
        Think of this page as a focused “wormhole” that tunnels straight into a single scenario:
        a decade-long global conflict followed by an overhaul of international institutions.
        It’s not a prediction, but a structured thought experiment — a way to explore risks,
        turning points, and long-range consequences.
      </p>
      <p>
        The timeline is organized year by year from 2026 to 2045, highlighting how events in
        Europe, the Indo-Pacific, and the Caribbean interact to produce a new post-war order.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="paths">
      <article class="path-card">
